HEADWORD: LTM
<hw>LTM</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Psychology, Neurophysiology)</fld>
<def>long-term memory, the term for the set of neurons and neural
processes responsible for the general store of information remembered
for more than a day.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> long-term memory.</syn>⟦br⟧
